						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Fragment of a slab built into the wall (outside), left of entrance into the raṅga-maṇḍapa of Śaṅkaraliṅga temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>13th Century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary record is in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">13th century A.D.</hi> It seems to register gifts of land, house-site and income from certain taxes probably to the Śaṅkaraliṅga temple. The details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
